<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Network-Unreachable on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/network-unreachable/</link><description>Recent content in Network-Unreachable on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/network-unreachable/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C errno ENETUNREACH — Network is unreachable Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-enetunreach/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-enetunreach/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-errno-enetunreach--network-is-unreachable-fix"&gt;[Solution] C errno ENETUNREACH — Network is unreachable Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When a network operation fails because the destination network is unreachable (no route exists), the system call sets &lt;code&gt;errno&lt;/code&gt; to &lt;code&gt;ENETUNREACH&lt;/code&gt;. This error occurs when the kernel&amp;rsquo;s routing table has no route to the destination network.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;No default gateway is configured on the system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The routing table does not have a route to the destination network.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The network interface is down, removing its associated routes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A firewall or routing policy blocks the route.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Check and fix routing configuration. Add a default gateway or specific routes.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C Network is unreachable: ENETUNREACH</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/network-unreachable/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/network-unreachable/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="network-is-unreachable-enetunreach"&gt;Network is unreachable: ENETUNREACH&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ENETUNREACH occurs when a network operation cannot reach the target network. This usually means no route exists to the destination, or the network interface is down.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: No route to destination
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;connect&lt;/span&gt;(sock, (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;struct&lt;/span&gt; sockaddr&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;addr, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(addr)); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// ENETUNREACH
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Network interface down
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// WiFi disconnected or ethernet unplugged
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: IPv6 not configured
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Trying to connect via IPv6 without IPv6 support
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-check-network-connectivity"&gt;Fix 1: Check network connectivity&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ip route show
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# or&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;route -n
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-check-interface-status"&gt;Fix 2: Check interface status&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ip link show
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# or&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ifconfig
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-add-route"&gt;Fix 3: Add route&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ip route add 10.0.0.0/8 via 192.168.1.1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/host-unreachable/"&gt;Host unreachable&lt;/a&gt; — EHOSTUNREACH.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/connection-refused-c/"&gt;Connection refused&lt;/a&gt; — ECONNREFUSED.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/operation-timed-out/"&gt;Connection timed out&lt;/a&gt; — ETIMEDOUT.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>